# Threat Intelligence Dashboard

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + CSS variables from design-reference.html
- **State**: React state + Context (no external state management)
- **Testing**: Vitest + React Testing Library
- **API**: Express mock server at localhost:3001, proxied to /api

## Project Structure

src/
├── api/ # API client functions (typed fetch wrappers)
├── components/ # React components (organized by feature)
│ ├── layout/ # AppLayout, Sidebar, PageHeader
│ ├── dashboard/ # StatsRow, Toolbar, Pagination
│ ├── table/ # DataTable, TableRow
│ ├── detail/ # DetailPanel
│ └── ui/ # Badge, Tag, Button, Input, ConfidenceBar
├── hooks/ # Custom hooks (useIndicators, useStats, useDebounce)
├── styles/ # global.css with design tokens
└── types/ # TypeScript interfaces (indicator.ts provided)

## API Endpoints

| Endpoint              | Method | Description                                          |
| --------------------- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `/api/indicators`     | GET    | Paginated list (page, limit, severity, type, search) |
| `/api/indicators/:id` | GET    | Single indicator details                             |
| `/api/stats`          | GET    | Summary statistics                                   |

## Key Types (from src/types/indicator.ts)

- `Indicator`: id, value, type, severity, source, firstSeen, lastSeen, tags, confidence
- `IndicatorType`: 'ip' | 'domain' | 'hash' | 'url'
- `Severity`: 'critical' | 'high' | 'medium' | 'low'
- `PaginatedResponse<T>`: data, total, page, totalPages

## Design Reference

Open `design-reference.html` in browser for exact specs. Key tokens:

- Fonts: DM Sans (UI), JetBrains Mono (technical data like IPs, hashes)
- Severity colors: critical=#ff4757, high=#ff8c42, medium=#ffc542, low=#48c774
- Brand: augur-blue=#6383ff
- Backgrounds: root=#0a0c10, surface=#0f1117, card=#1a1e28

## Conventions

- Use TypeScript strictly (no `any`)
- Colocate tests with source files (`Component.tsx` + `Component.test.tsx`)
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Handle loading, error, and empty states for all async operations
- Debounce search inputs (300ms)
